## 5. Quality Validation

### 5.1 The 4U's Headline Formula

Developed by Michael Masterson (AWAI).

| Element | Definition | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| **Useful** | Shows benefit | "How to write headlines that convert" |
| **Urgent** | Creates time pressure | "Before your next launch" |
| **Unique** | Differentiates | "The counterintuitive approach" |
| **Ultra-specific** | Provides details | "7 formulas with 23 examples" |

**Scoring:** Rate 1-4 for each. Target: 3.5+ average.

---

### 5.2 Copy Review Checklist

Before shipping any copy:

```
□ One Mississippi test (understood in <2 seconds?)
□ Every line visualizable (concrete, not abstract?)
□ Every claim falsifiable (provable, not adjective soup?)
□ Competitor couldn't sign it (unique angle?)
□ Kaplan's Law applied (every word earns its place?)
□ No paragraph >2 lines
□ First line hooks to second (curiosity → payoff)
□ Reviewed in context (mocked up where it lives)
□ Word count reduced: Started ___ → Ended ___
```

### Red Flag Words (Automatic rewrite needed)

| Red Flag | Problem |
|----------|---------|
| "Innovative solution" | Abstract, unfalsifiable |
| "Best in class" | Generic, competitor could say it |
| "Seamless experience" | Can't visualize |
| "Transform your..." | Abstract verb |
| "Cutting-edge" | Meaningless buzzword |
| Multiple adjectives | Hiding weak nouns |
| "And" 3+ times | Scope creep |

